---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Ahmad Piraiee, strategist, venture builder, and execution partner.">
  <section class="about-profile">
    <figure class="profile-card">
      <img src="/assets/brand/ahmad-piraiee-portrait-new.png" alt="Portrait of Ahmad Piraiee" />
      <figcaption>
        <span>Strategist</span>
        <strong>Ahmad Piraiee</strong>
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <div class="profile-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">/ 02 / About</p>
      <h1>Turning uncertainty into execution.</h1>
      <p>
        I help founders, companies, investors, and innovation teams make better decisions
        before they commit time, money, and people.
      </p>
      <p>
        For more than 20 years, I have worked where technology, business, and human behavior
        intersect - building ventures, launching innovation programs, guiding founders, and
        helping organizations navigate change. My role is not to apply generic frameworks. It
        is to understand what is unique about each challenge, identify what truly matters, and
        create the shortest path from uncertainty to execution.
      </p>

      <div class="profile-stat-grid">
        <div>
          <strong>20+</strong>
          <span>Years of experience</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>95K+</strong>
          <span>Professionals in my network</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>1K+</strong>
          <span>Events, workshops & talks</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>2.5K+</strong>
          <span>Founders and teams mentored</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-story">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Background</p>
      <h2>Pattern recognition built through experience.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="story-copy">
      <p>
        My background combines computer engineering, behavioral science, marketing, and
        socioeconomic research - not as credentials, but as different ways of understanding
        how people, technology, and organizations make decisions.
      </p>
      <p>
        Throughout my career I have helped build startup accelerators, innovation programs,
        venture initiatives, communities, and international partnerships. I have worked with
        organizations including MIT Enterprise Forum, PwC, mBank, Venture Cafe, CIC Warsaw,
        Startup Grind, and numerous startups, corporations, universities, and public
        institutions.
      </p>
      <p>
        Across thousands of conversations with founders, executives, investors, and innovation
        leaders, I have learned one thing:
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Most organizations do not fail because they execute poorly. They fail because they solve the wrong problem.</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        That is where I create the most value.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-services">
    <p class="eyebrow">Capabilities</p>
    <h2>How I help organizations move forward.</h2>
    <div class="accordion-list large-accordion">
      <details open>
        <summary>Strategic Clarity</summary>
        <p>
          Identify the real challenge, challenge assumptions, validate opportunities, and
          define a direction worth pursuing before significant resources are committed.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Venture & Innovation Building</summary>
        <p>
          Design and launch innovation initiatives, accelerators, venture programs, AI
          initiatives, and new business opportunities that create measurable outcomes.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Interim Leadership</summary>
        <p>
          Embed within organizations to lead strategic initiatives, build internal capability,
          and accelerate execution until the team can operate independently.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Founder Advisory & Mentoring</summary>
        <p>
          Help founders make better decisions, validate business models, sharpen positioning,
          avoid common mistakes, and find product-market fit without losing what makes their
          business unique.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>AI & Business Transformation</summary>
        <p>
          Apply AI where it creates genuine business value - not because it is fashionable,
          but because it solves a real problem, saves time, improves decisions, or unlocks
          new opportunities.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Ecosystem & Strategic Partnerships</summary>
        <p>
          Connect startups, corporations, investors, universities, and institutions to create
          partnerships, commercial opportunities, and long-term innovation ecosystems.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Speaking, Workshops & Education</summary>
        <p>
          Deliver practical talks, executive workshops, university lectures, and moderation
          focused on entrepreneurship, innovation, AI, leadership, and strategic thinking.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-philosophy">
    <p class="eyebrow">Philosophy</p>
    <blockquote>Clarity before execution.</blockquote>
    <p>Moving faster only helps if you are moving in the right direction.</p>
    <p>
      The best founders, companies, and leaders do not succeed because they have all the
      answers. They succeed because they ask better questions, recognize patterns others
      overlook, and make better decisions before committing resources.
    </p>
    <p>
      That is the role I aim to play in every engagement: bringing clarity to complexity,
      turning uncertainty into action, and leaving organizations stronger than I found them.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
